      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "0aba19eb2866f09760bcf7d21b2c50b3b19ed152",
            "subject": "LU-0000 lov: Basic do-no-harm lov IO support"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-08-09 20:08:08.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-09-04 23:38:44.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 utils: fix EC setstripe validation timing",
        "message": "LU-0000 utils: fix EC setstripe validation timing\n\nFix validation logic for EC (erasure coding) setstripe\ncommands that was incorrectly rejecting valid EC layouts.\n\nThe issue was that EC validation occurred before the final\ncomponent was processed, causing false positives when\nchecking if at least one EC component was created.\n\nThis change moves the EC component count validation to\nafter component processing is complete, while keeping\nbasic validation (conflicts with -c, setstripe-only)\nearlier in the flow.\n\nBefore this fix:\n- lfs setstripe --ec 4+2 -E EOF file would fail with\n  \"--ec requires explicit component end with -E\"\n- Tests 3a and 3c in sanity-ec.sh would skip\n\nAfter this fix:\n- Single and multi-component EC layouts work correctly\n- All sanity-ec tests pass except 0d (needs >= 4 OSTs)\n- EC file creation and IO operations work end-to-end\n\nTest-Parameters: forjanitoronly\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Id766d7b3e1a024e3d333d2915e6f1c8ad22d358f\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
  "requirements": [],
  "submit_records": []
